titlestmt.titleproper: Finding aid to the Classes of 1879-1890 records CA.MS.01023
titlestmt.author: Madison White

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2019-02-25 11:44:02 -0500.

change.item: Finding aids for each class records were combined into this meta record, with additions from recent accessions

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for use without restriction beyond the standard terms and conditions of Smith College Special Collections.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Whenever donation information for a particular set of material is known, it is included in the finding aid below. However, a majority of the material was not formally accessioned and its origins are not currently known.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection brings together twelve record groups that are arranged chronologically, one per graduating class. However, since some materials are placed in a class record group based on when they were created, and not by whom, materials relelvant to a class may exist in more than one series.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please use the following format when citing materials from this collection:
Classes of 1879-1890 records, Box #, Smith College Archives, CA-MS-01023, Smith College Special Collections, Northampton, Massachusetts.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Classes of 1879-1890 records consist of individual class notes, examinations, papers and class letters, correspondence, photographs, scrapbooks, songbooks as well as reunion materials of the same nature, all related to or dating from the time periods during which these classes were students at Smith College.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Materials in this collection may be governed by copyright. For reproductions of materials that are governed by fair use as defined under U. S. Copyright Law, no permission to cite or publish is required. Researchers are responsible for determining who may hold materials' copyrights and obtaining approval from them. Researchers do not need anything further from Smith College Special Collections to move forward with their use.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Class of 1879 was the first graduating class of Smith College.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: The Class of 1879 records were processed by Elisha Winkler in 2006.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Class of 1879 Records contain materials describing the history of the students of the first graduating class of Smith College. Types of materials include black and white photographs, programs, magazine and newspaper articles, lists of students, letters, correspondence, and information about the Class of 1879's commencement and reunions.
